=== sgas-wlcg-tool ===

sgas-wlcg-tool is a command line utility for managing the WLCG schema in the
SGAS database. It can be used to inspect and modify the mapping between
machines, sites, countries, tiers and VOs that is needed for WLCG accounting.

The tool reads the database connection string from the SGAS configuration file
(default: /etc/sgas.conf). An alternate config file can be specified with the
-c flag:

    sgas-wlcg-tool -c /path/to/sgas.conf <command> [options]


--- Commands ---

show    List machines with their associated site, country and tier/VO mappings.
add     Add a machine (and site/country if needed) with tier/VO mappings.
del     Remove machines, sites, countries, site associations or tier/VO rows.
edit    Rename a machine, site or country.


--- show ---

List all machines with their country, site and tier:VO mappings:

    sgas-wlcg-tool show

The output can be filtered by one or more of the following options:

    --machine MACHINE    Filter by machine name
    --site SITE          Filter by site name
    --country COUNTRY    Filter by country name
    --tier TIER          Filter by tier name, or "tier_name:vo_name"

Examples:

    sgas-wlcg-tool show --country "Norway"
    sgas-wlcg-tool show --site "FOO"
    sgas-wlcg-tool show --tier "ndgf-t1"
    sgas-wlcg-tool show --tier "ndgf-t1:atlas"


--- add ---

Add a machine together with its site and country (if needed), and associate it
with one or more tiers.

    sgas-wlcg-tool add \
        --machine MACHINE \
        --site SITE \
        --tier TIER:VO \
        [--country COUNTRY] \
        [--tier TIER:VO ...]

Options:

    --machine MACHINE    (required) Machine name as it appears in the database
    --site SITE          Site name to associate with the machine
    --tier TIER:VO       Tier and VO, e.g. "ndgf-t1:atlas".
                         Use '*' for vo_name to match all VOs.
                         Can be repeated to set multiple tier/VO rows.
    --country COUNTRY    Country of the site. Required if the site does not
                         already exist.

Examples:

    # Add the machine kurvi.tasch.bx from the site FOO in Borduria, which will
    # run atlas jobs for ndgf-t1, and cms jobs for borduria-t2
    sgas-wlcg-tool add \
        --machine "kurvi.tasch.bx" \
        --country "Borduria" \
        --site "FOO" \
        --tier "ndgf-t1:atlas" \
        --tier "borduria-t2:cms"

    # Jobs from all VOs on kurvi.tasch.bx are ran for ndgf-t1
    sgas-wlcg-tool add \
        --machine "kurvi.tasch.bx" \
        --tier "ndgf-t1:*"


--- del ---

The del command covers several removal operations depending on which options
are given.


Remove specific tier/VO rows from a machine:

    sgas-wlcg-tool del --machine MACHINE --tier TIER:VO [--tier TIER:VO ...]

    Example:

        sgas-wlcg-tool del --machine "kurvi.tasch.bx" --tier "ndgf-t1:atlas"


Disassociate a machine from a site:

    sgas-wlcg-tool del --machine MACHINE --site SITE

    Example:

        sgas-wlcg-tool del --machine "kurvi.tasch.bx" --site "FOO"


Disassociate a machine from a site and remove a tier in one operation:

    sgas-wlcg-tool del --machine MACHINE --site SITE --tier TIER:VO


Fully remove a machine:

    sgas-wlcg-tool del --machine MACHINE

    This removes the machine from the machinename table together with all its
    tier/VO rows (wlcg.tiers), site associations (wlcg.machinename_site_junction)
    and scale factor entries (hostscalefactors_data). All removals happen inside
    a single transaction.

    This operation is refused if the machine has any usage records in the
    usagedata table.

    Example:

        sgas-wlcg-tool del --machine "kurvi.tasch.bx"


Remove a site:

    sgas-wlcg-tool del --site SITE

    Removes the site from wlcg.sites. This operation is refused if any machine
    is still associated with the site in wlcg.machinename_site_junction, or if
    the site has any pledge entries in wlcg.pledges.

    Example:

        sgas-wlcg-tool del --site "FOO"


Remove a country:

    sgas-wlcg-tool del --country COUNTRY

    Removes the country from wlcg.countries. This operation is refused if the
    country still has any sites in wlcg.sites or any pledge entries in
    wlcg.pledges. --country cannot be combined with any other option.

    Example:

        sgas-wlcg-tool del --country "Borduria"


--- edit ---

Rename a machine, site or country. Exactly one of --machine, --site or
--country must be given, along with --renameto.

Rename a machine:

    sgas-wlcg-tool edit --machine MACHINE --renameto NEWNAME

    Example:

        sgas-wlcg-tool edit --machine "kurvi.tash.bx" --renameto "kurvi.tasch.bx"


Rename a site:

    sgas-wlcg-tool edit --site SITE --renameto NEWNAME

    Example:

        sgas-wlcg-tool edit --site "FOO" --renameto "BAR"


Rename a country:

    sgas-wlcg-tool edit --country COUNTRY --renameto NEWNAME

    Example:

        sgas-wlcg-tool edit --country "Bodruria" --renameto "Borduria"
